'''Joanna McClelland Glass''' (born October 1936 in [[Saskatoon]], Saskatchewan, Canada) is [[playwright]].<ref name="nothof2009">{{Cite web
|first=Anne
|last=Nothof
|title=Glass, Joanna McClelland
|url=http://www.canadiantheatre.com/dict.pl?term=Glass%2C%20Joanna%20McClelland
|work=Canadian theatre encyclopedia
|publisher=[[Athabasca University]]
|date=2009-04-02
|accessdate=2009-06-27}}</ref> She became an American citizen in 1962.<ref name="nothof2009" />

==Plays==
*1972 ''Canadian Gothic''
*1972 ''American Modern''
*1975 ''Artichoke''
*1980 ''To Grandmother's House We Go''
*1983 ''Play Memory''
*1989 ''Yesteryear''
*1993 ''If We Are Women''
*2004 ''Trying''
*2008 ''Palmer Park''<ref name="nothof2009" />

==Novels==
*1975 ''Reflections on a Mountain Summer'' (Knopf)
*1984 ''Woman Wanted'' (St. Martin's)<ref name="nothof2009" />

==See also==
*''[[Woman Wanted]]'', film adapted from novel.<ref name="nothof2009" />

